<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,835]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[473,772,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[473,772,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Afrasura submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with the discal dot and marginal dots blackish in colour, whereas in 
<taxonomicName box="[390,490,191,216]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis box="[390,490,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they have the same colour of the bands; fringes buff (
<bibRefCitation author="Kiriakoff" box="[1172,1394,190,216]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" refString="Kiriakoff, S. G. (1958) Ruwenzori Expedition, 1952, vol. I, 2. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 1 - 39." type="book chapter" year="1958">
Kiriakoff, 
<number box="[1307,1374,190,216]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="1958.0">1958</number>
: 
<number box="[1377,1394,190,216]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,323,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[151,323,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, yellowish-white in 
<taxonomicName box="[564,657,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis box="[564,657,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,835]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,267,293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Description.</emphasis>
Ƥ wingspan 
<quantity box="[510,598,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
. Forewing upperside ground colour whitish; pattern light brown. Only one roughly straight basal band discernible; the median and postmedian ones join to form a marbled pattern; one dot at the distal ending of the cell; sub-marginal series of four dots. Hindwing upperside ground colour same as in forewings. Forewing underside with bands less evident, and only two submarginal dots. Hindwing underside as in upperside. Fringes of all wings yellowish-white. Head, thorax, and all appendices yellowishwhite. Antennae ciliated. Labial palpi slender, slightly inclined downwards, not extending beyond the frons. Spurs 
<number box="[226,274,500,526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="0.2">0, 2</number>
, 
<number box="[287,305,500,526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
. A 
<number box="[340,354,500,526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="7.0">7</number>
large membranous, but stiff, with its cephalic margin forming two sterno-pleural pouches. A 
<number box="[175,189,538,564]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
small and membranous. Female dorsal pheromone glands shorter than posterior apophyses. Male unknown. Ƥ antrum large, sub-cylindrical, slightly narrower at its cephalic ending. Ductus bursae membranous, short, forming connection between long antrum and cervix, comprising thick membranous tissue and enclosing two clusters of thorns. Corpus bursae membranous, sub-spherical, about two times the cervix, with small spread thorns inside. Signum small, formed by minute thorns in a rosette. Ductus seminalis arising from corpus bursae in cephalic position, rather than from the cervix as is usually typical in 
<taxonomicName box="[1305,1409,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1305,1409,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Afrasura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,835]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,339,770,796]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Etymology</emphasis>
. From the Latin verb 
<emphasis box="[623,732,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">discerno</emphasis>
(distinguish), reflecting the fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[1262,1317,770,796]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
has been distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[379,551,809,834]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[379,551,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
